recommendations.title: Google CEO Sundar Pichai Faced Intense Pushback From Employees. His Response Is a Masterclass in Leading People
recommendations.excerpt: Over the past two years, Google's CEO, Sundar Pichai, has faced increased pushback from employees, most recently at an employee meeting in March. Employees there complained that the company is falling behind on issues like compensation and how the company reviews performance.

recommendations.title: What Your Profile Picture Says About Your Personality, According to a Life Coach
recommendations.excerpt: What’s in a profile picture? Well, quite a lot according to life coach Francesca Tighinean.

recommendations.title: Huge Study Identifies The 'Optimal' Amount of Sleep From Middle Age Onwards
recommendations.excerpt: Sleep – a lot like eating food – is one of those things we need to live, but seemingly there are plenty of ways to do it wrong.   A new study has weighed into the debate.

recommendations.title: The Overlooked Reason Russia’s Invasion Is Floundering
recommendations.excerpt: Airpower should have been one of Russia’s greatest advantages over Ukraine.

recommendations.title: An Indian startup endorses the “right to nap”
recommendations.excerpt: Sleeping on the job is now cool.

recommendations.title: A millennial who achieved financial independence at age 30 shares his top strategies for earning more money
recommendations.excerpt: Grant Sabatier started with virtually nothing before achieving financial independence. In August 2010, two months after getting laid off from his first job, his checking account hit an all-time low: $2.26.

recommendations.title: The Myth of the Genius Tech Inventor
recommendations.excerpt: It’s practically an insult in Silicon Valley to say that an executive is extremely capable at running a company. Inventors, not great managers, are often the ones celebrated in technology.

recommendations.title: Climate scientists say South Asia's heat wave (120F!) is a sign of what's to come
recommendations.excerpt: Summer has arrived in South Asia WAY too early. A punishing heat wave has pushed temperatures past 120F (50C) in some areas. Some schools have closed early for the summer. Dozens of people have people have died of heat stroke.

recommendations.title: What the Best Presenters Do Differently
recommendations.excerpt: According to Pulitzer Prize–winning historian Doris Kearns Goodwin, villagers would come from far and wide to hear Abraham Lincoln, then a prairie lawyer with a gift for storytelling. Lincoln didn’t have the benefit of modern technology.

recommendations.title: In Test Tubes, RNA Molecules Evolve Into a Tiny Ecosystem
recommendations.excerpt: When researchers gave a genetic molecule the ability to replicate, it evolved over time into a complex network of “hosts” and “parasites” that both competed and cooperated to survive.

recommendations.title: How to Turn a Volcano Into an Oven
recommendations.excerpt: From hot-springs stew to lava-baked pizza, a tour of the world’s most amazing volcanically-cooked meals.

recommendations.title: Ukraine conflict: What is Nato and how has it responded to Russia's invasion?
recommendations.excerpt: Finland has said it wants to join Nato and neighbouring Sweden is expected to make a decision soon.

recommendations.title: The Dish Our Customers Will Never Let Us Take Off the Menu
recommendations.excerpt: Chargrilled broccoli with slivers of fried garlic and red chile is a fixture at Yotam Ottolenghi’s delis. There’s a good reason.

recommendations.title: Anxiety can be good for you
recommendations.excerpt: Dr Tracy Dennis-Tiwary was a professor of psychology, immersed in research – evaluating which mental health treatments worked and why – when she first became aware of an uptick in anxiety. This was some 15 years ago in New York City.

recommendations.title: The True Story of Dogstar, Keanu Reeves' Mediocre '90s Rock Band That Toured the World
recommendations.excerpt: In an excerpt from the new book Keanu Reeves: Most Triumphant, Alex Pappademas traces the origins of an LA band that somehow ended up opening for Weezer and David Bowie—and wasn't even the only band named Dogstar in town.

recommendations.title: What is watermelon snow?
recommendations.excerpt: It's also known as blood snow, pink snow, or red snow.

recommendations.title: Mental health: 8 hidden signs of imposter syndrome, according to a therapist
recommendations.excerpt: Imposter syndrome is often defined as doubting yourself or feeling like a “fake” – but, as mentioned by therapist Abby Rawlinson, there are hidden signs of this that go way beyond what we know. Imposter syndrome is something that many of us deal with – particularly as women.

recommendations.title: Love is both wonderful and a dangerous evolutionary trick
recommendations.excerpt: We are all experts in love.

recommendations.title: Mexico City and the pitfalls of becoming a remote work destination
recommendations.excerpt: The city has become a remote work playground for expats. Meanwhile, rising housing prices and inflation have made it more unaffordable for locals.

recommendations.title: Explained | How are Supreme Court judges appointed in India?
recommendations.excerpt: The story so far: Gauhati High Court Chief Justice Sudhanshu Dhulia and Gujarat High Court Judge Justice Jamshed Burjor Pardiwala were appointed as Supreme Court judges on Monday. The ceremony was held in an auditorium of the Supreme Court’s additional building complex.

recommendations.title: A Crumbling Russian ‘Spyville’ Returns to Polish Hands
recommendations.excerpt: A Warsaw housing complex built in the 1970s and rented by Russia was reputed to be a nest of spies. The city’s government has seized the site and pledged to hand it over to the Ukrainian community.

recommendations.title: 'Buy now, pay later' sends TikTok generation spiraling into debt
recommendations.excerpt: “Buy now, pay later” may be jeopardizing Gen Z's financial future.

recommendations.title: Small Drones Are Giving Ukraine an Unprecedented Edge
recommendations.excerpt: In the snowy streets of the north Ukrainian town of Trostyanets, the Russian missile system fires rockets every second. Tanks and military vehicles are parked on either side of the blasting artillery system, positioned among houses and near the town’s railway system.

recommendations.title: As Boris Johnson heads to Finland, what will it mean if the Finns join NATO?
recommendations.excerpt: A decision is imminent on whether the historically neutral country, which fought the Soviets in WWII and lost, will seek membership of the defensive pact. We look at what it means for Finns and for other NATO countries, including the UK.

recommendations.title: The Pop Song That’s Uniting India and Pakistan
recommendations.excerpt: The writer and musician Ali Sethi has created an unconventional hit with “Pasoori.”

recommendations.title: Are sanctions against Russia working?
recommendations.excerpt: The unprecedented penalties are dismantling the Russian economy, even as Moscow tries to find ways to ease the pain. The United States and its allies imposed unprecedented economic sanctions on Russia in the wake of its full-scale invasion of Ukraine.

recommendations.title: How to Be a Compassionate Manager in a Heartless Organization
recommendations.excerpt: Research shows that employees who work for compassionate managers are 25% more engaged in their jobs, 20% more committed to the organization, and 11% less likely to burn out. But too many organizations seem not to have gotten the memo yet.

recommendations.title: Where Our Thoughts Come From: How Microemotions Affect Spontaneous Thought
recommendations.excerpt: Emotions play a key role in many types of spontaneous thoughts. Even microemotions—which are often fleeting and unconscious — can affect thoughts and influence attention.

recommendations.title: 18 Recipes You Should Learn by Heart
recommendations.excerpt: Memorize these easy dishes and techniques, and you’ll have an arsenal of easy meals at hand. Everyone has one or two — or 20! — recipes that they know by heart.

recommendations.title: A Veterinarian’s Perspective on Writing Animals
recommendations.excerpt: Pets pick up on plenty that their humans fail to notice, and they're always aware of one's true emotional state.
